The paper deals with the problem of mobile robot localization, which is a core topic in robotics and falls under the category of robotics and control (cs.RO). The proposed method uses probabilistic algorithms and Bayesian formulation, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of sensor data, which is a common theme in computer vision (cs.CV). The problem of tracking equally probable poses for the robot is related to control theory and system dynamics (cs.SY). Finally, the use of weighted samples and clusters is a common technique in machine learning and statistical inference (cs.LG).
